This agreement is between you, the user of Freetour.com website(s) and Applications, (“You” or “User”) and FREETOUR.com (“FREETOUR.com”, “we”, “us”). Where “website(s)”, “platform(s)”, “app(s)” or “application(s)” are mentioned, it is assumed to include all FREETOUR.com site(s), mobile optimised site(s), and apps.
Use of the Website is conditional on that accepting and understanding the Terms of Use and Privacy Policy. Any further use of the Website is indicative of your having read and understood same.
'The tour provider' is the organizer of the tour which is offering services (Tour) for booking or sale via the website(s). 'Tour' should be considered as inclusive of all services, includes, added value and other offered by the tour provider displayed 'as is' on the website(s).
You confirm that you are of legal age to lawfully use Freetour.com web-sites & services, to enter into a contract and that you are solely responsible for all uses performed on said sites / services by you, even if on the behalf of another. Where for all uses performed on said sites / services by you on the behalf of another, you confirm that you have the express permission to provide required and voluntary data pertaining to said other.
You understand that Freetour.com is a platform which facilitates your booking of tours with independent tour providers and that Freetour.com does not own, operate or provide tours. Furthermore, you understand that you are entering into a contract with the tour provider and not Freetour.com, our sites or services. The tour provider is solely responsible and liable for fulfilling said contract on their part and providing you with tour service as booked or with an alternative to your satisfaction where applicable.
It is the responsibility of the tour provider to ensure the accuracy, legitimacy and correctness of all content and information pertaining to their tour and services as displayed on Freetour.com website(s). Freetour.com are in no way responsible for the quality of any tour or services booked on the site(s).
The information on this Website does not constitute an offer binding to us. Binding agreements with suppliers of activities available on the Website require a booking request through the FREETOUR.com Platform and the Tour Provider’s acceptance of the booking request according to the General Terms and Conditions.
Supported Currencies
All transactions in FREETOUR.com are processed in EURO. However, the website and APPs have the flexibility of displaying a real time conversion to any of the available currencies.
All currency conversions displayed on Freetour.com sites are calculated by using an exchange rate derived from a third-party reputable currency conversion website in real time.
Customers can book any paid activity, displaying prices in any preferred currency that is available, but the payment & transaction at the checkout process will be carried out in EURO only.
Customer credit card is charged in EURO, therefore, the email price breakdown and payment receipts are presented in EURO currency only.
Third-party fees
The price displayed on FREETOUR.com website & APPs may differ from the sum a customer is charged, regardless of the payment being processed in EURO due to bank fees for international transactions, currency conversion from user’s local currency to EURO, other fees.
FREETOUR.com is not responsible for these fees. Please contact your bank or credit card company to learn about any extra fees when purchasing in EURO.
Booking process.
Booking Free Tours
The Freetour.com platform facilitates the booking of ‘free tours’ by free tour providers, whereby you are free to pay what you feel the tour experience was worth directly to the tour provider at the end of the tour experience, in person, on the day of the tour as booked. You are not required to pay any amount at the point of booking through the platform.
Freetour.com remains responsible for all transaction amounts carried out on our site, including facilitating charge-backs and refunds of said amounts where required. We are not responsible for other amounts paid and processed outside of our site in relation to tour service booked, including but not limited to, payments you make directly to the tour provider or any costs incurred during the service for add-ons, local taxes, or other purchases.
A ‘confirmed booking’ registers your request to join the tour with the tour provider. The tour provider reserves the right to reject your booking or deny you service in the event of over-booking or if tour capacity has already been reached upon your arrival to the tour.
Where available, you can choose to make a ‘guaranteed’ booking which requires log in with social media as way of verification. This guarantees you a spot, held specifically for you by the tour provider, on the tour and protected in the event of over-booking or tour maximum capacity being reached.
Some free tour providers will only accept bookings verified by social media log in, as a way to verify bookings and customers attending the specific activity.
You will receive a booking confirmation via email shortly after completing the booking process.
Booking Paid Tours
The Freetour.com platform also facilitates the booking of ‘paid tours’ services offered by tour providers.
Fully paid at the point of booking
Some activities are possible to book only if paying the entire sum at the point of booking.
Bookings are free to cancel up to 24 hours prior tour date.
Pay on arrival
Some activities are possible to book with no payment at the point of booking. In such cases, you are required to pay the entire sum on arrival, at the activity meeting point.
You confirm that all information submitted by you to Freetour.com, including Credit card / Debit card details, are complete and accurate and that you have been granted the required permissions and authorizations to use said card.
You will receive a booking confirmation via email shortly after completing the booking process, provided that all information submitted is correct and there are sufficient funds available to the credit / debit card used to complete the transaction.
Cancellation Policies
Free tours
cancellation policy: you are free to cancel a booking anytime. We kindly remind you to cancel bookings you cannot arrive for. Being reported as absent decreases your customer level points and the benefits you can enjoy.
Paid Activities
cancellation policy: Free Cancellation up to 24 hours before the activity starts. Late cancellation or your non-arrival is not refundable.
Refunds
A refund can be applied to bookings which are fully paid at the point of booking.
Refunds are executed automatically at the moment of cancelation or rejection of a paid activity.
In case of no refund received, please contact support@freetour.com with your booking confirmation number.
While we endeavour to process refunds in as timely a manner as possible, please allow sufficient time for refunds to take place which can depend on different factors such as your card provider and geographical location.
General booking conditions
In making a booking you agree to the tour providers' policies, including all relevant no-show and cancellation policies as displayed or set out in their profile. Accordingly, in the event of your failing to comply with said policies, including failure to arrive by your agreed time or failure to cancel your booking within the permitted time-frame as set out by the tour provider, you authorise Freetour.com to charge your credit / debit card and retain on behalf of the tour provider an amount not greater than the balance due for the service as booked after the service fee paid at the point of booking. Freetour.com may inform you of the charge in such an event, as a courtesy.
By making a booking, you permit FREETOUR.com to initiate payment, or a series of payments, on your behalf in relation to the products purchased which may require recurring payments, depending on the related policies opted into at the point of booking. Payment may be processed in real-time or at a later time as an off-session payment. You authorise FREETOUR.com to utilise your saved card details for these purposes and for future bookings you may make on the platform, for a simpler booking process.
Credit / Debit card details are entered on a secure page and transferred using SSL technology. Payment is processed by a secure & reputable payment portal.
It is your responsibility to notify the tour provider directly to make any amendments to your booking or to inform them of any special requirements / facilities that you or a member of your party may require.
The listing of tour providers on Freetour.com websites should not be considered as a specific recommendation by Freetour.com or that the tour provider will be suitable for the user's purpose or of any particular quality.
Freetour.com may offer you the opportunity to review the tour provider post-service in relation to your tour experience and your opinion. The ranking and rating attributed to tour products on our sites are influenced by this feedback and your review and rating may be visible on our site(s).
User Profile
You can create a registered user profile on the platform without making a booking.
When you make an initial booking without having already created a user profile, a profile will automatically be generated for you and you will be granted access to this profile to use for any future bookings.
Your registered user profile consists of information you supply, including first & last names, email, date of birth, contact phone number, nationality, gender and profile photo.
We will retain submitted personal information for as long as you have a personal registered user profile on the platform. You can request deletion of your user profile and associated information at any time by emailing
support@freetour.com
All personal data provided to Freetour.com is treated, controlled and processed in accordance with local laws (that of Switzerland) and GDPR protocol. The security of your personal information and privacy is hugely important to us and we have taken sufficient measures to ensure this is controlled in a consistently secure manner. We will never provide your details to any third party. See Privacy Policy for more detail about your personal information and data collection and handling.
